gov.nih.nlm.meme.common
Interface Rank

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable
All Known Implementing Classes:
Rank.Default
public interface Rank
extends Comparable

Generically represents a rank. This class exists to support the Rankable interface which allows other classes to have ranks associated with them.

Ranks can be constructed as either int or String. In the background, the rank is represented as a string, but when compared if the rank was constructed as an int, it should be compared as an int. The default implementation adheres to this.

Author:
MEME Group
